; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: solid; background-color: #ccc;">The Financial Times reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The company=E2=80=99s reputation has been batt=
ered by allegations that Carta staff used confidential information to solic=
it investors in start-ups to sell their stakes in the secondary market with=
out consent from the start-ups themselves. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Henry Ward, the company=E2=80=99s chief execut=
ive, said in a blog post on Monday night that the lacklustre performance an=
d ultimate closure of the trading platform was =E2=80=9Cmy greatest failure=
 and disappointment=E2=80=9D.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CBecause we have the data, if we are t=
rading secondaries, people will always worry that we are using the data, ev=
en if we are not. So we have decided to prioritise trust, and exit the seco=
ndary trading business,=E2=80=9D he wrote.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">What I said yesterday is that =E2=80=9Cwe=E2=
=80=99ll give you an inexpensive service and monetize it by using the data =
for targeted advertising=E2=80=9D is really=C2=A0<em>the=C2=A0</em>great bu=
siness model of the 21st century, and that Carta=E2=80=99s service would se=
em to generate=C2=A0<em>very=C2=A0</em>valuable data for targeted advertisi=
ng. (The advertising is =E2=80=9Csell your shares of this hot startup,=E2=
=80=9D targeted to actual shareholders.) It is rough, for a hot startup, to=
 disavow that model. Perhaps it is a=C2=A0lesson in the dangers of monetizi=
ng too early.</p>
